<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Adulterate2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Adulterate,</orth> adj. 1) unfaithful to the marriage bed: <bibl n="shak. luc" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1645</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 42</bibl>.<lb />2) unchaste, lewd: <cit><quote>why should others' false a. eyes give salutation to my sportive blood?</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 121.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 121, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his foul a. heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 175" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 175</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the a. Hastings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.69" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 69</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>